description: Set the storage type of a trap configuration to 'other' or 'nonVolatile'.
'nonVolatile' -> the trap configuration will always be restored after a CXU reboot
'other' -> the trap configuration will be stored in RAM (like 'volatile') and
therefore lost upon reboot
-> additional to the standard 'volatile' definition, this entry is 'timeLimited'
which means automatically deleted, if a snmp management session with
equal IP address was removed from sheSystemManagementSessionTable by session timeout
Other settings will not be accepted.
